A SEX attacker pounced on a 16-year-old girl as she sat on a Glasgow bus.&nbsp;Detectives are hunting for a man who sexually assaulted the teenager on Thursday on a number 7A bus from the city centre.The incident happened at around 4.30pm after the woman got on the bus at McDonalds near Jamaica Street.A man, who was also at the stop, got on the bus at the same time.The young woman made her way towards the rear of the bus and sat down.The suspect then followed her and sat beside her where he sexually assaulted her.The teenager then got off the bus at Skirsa Street in Possil. She has been left extremely distressed by the ordeal.The suspect is described as black, around 6ft in height, in his late 40s to early 50s with black hair, which is greying. The suspect also has no teeth.Officers have been gathering CCTV images and are trying to trace passengers from the bus.Detective Sergeant Alan Cuthbert said: &quot;I'm appealing to anyone who may have been on the bus and who may have noticed this man when he got on.&quot;If you were a passenger on the bus and saw the man please do contact us, did you see where the man got off the bus, any information could prove vital is helping us trace the man responsible for this assault which has left a young woman very upset.&quot;Anyone with any information is asked to contact officers at Maryhill Police Office on the non-emergency number, 101.